CRITICAL STRESS REDUCTION

    </h3>
    <p class="italic"> 
        
Critical stress reduction is not about managing stress—it’s about honoring the body’s natural intelligence when it has been pushed beyond its capacity to cope. In moments of overwhelm, trauma, or long-term depletion, the nervous system becomes flooded, frozen, or hyper-reactive. Critical stress reduction offers a path back to balance through breath, grounded presence, gentle somatic awareness, and deep listening. It is a sacred pause that interrupts the cycle of survival, allowing the body, mind, and heart to begin remembering safety, stillness, and trust. True healing begins not when we push through, but when we allow ourselves to soften into what is—and meet it with compassion.         </p>
